1
00:00:38,220 --> 00:00:38,900
Have a drink.

2
00:00:41,820 --> 00:00:44,600
I know that we haven't been
 seeing each other lately.

3
00:00:45,210 --> 00:00:47,520
I hope you won't be upset at me...

4
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,520
for calling only when I need a favor.

5
00:00:52,380 --> 00:00:53,240
Sorry to bother you.

6
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:56,190
Actually, I should be the one doing this.

7
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:59,930
But I just got transferred to a new section
at work, and things have been hectic.

8
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:05,340
You know my wedding will be held in Hawaii.

9
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:11,820
I need someone who can secure
a good venue for the post-reception party.

10
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:15,840
Your company published 
guide books for Hawaii, right?

11
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,150
Were you in charge of those?

12
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,110
On occasion, yes.

13
00:01:22,510 --> 00:01:25,480
Awesome! You must have been there 
several times then, haven't you?

14
00:01:26,830 --> 00:01:30,190
Well...

15
00:01:32,090 --> 00:01:33,130
Will you help?

16
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,990
I'd be so grateful.

17
00:01:43,050 --> 00:01:45,480
Well then. Please give it some thought.

18
00:01:46,910 --> 00:01:48,910
– See you.
– See you.

19
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:56,300
Turn her down, Minori.

20
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:04,820
None of our old classmates wound go to
Hawaii just for a post-reception party.

21
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:08,790
It'll just be Aiko's fellow cabin attendants 
and her fiance’s clients.

22
00:02:09,070 --> 00:02:09,970
It doesn't matter.

23
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:14,210
Her fiancé is rich and
has big-name clients, right?

24
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:17,710
No one will pay any attention to us.

25
00:02:18,330 --> 00:02:24,020
This party is just an excuse to let
his clients hook up with her colleagues.

26
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:27,980
Aiko just wants ordinary girls
like us there as hired help.

27
00:02:27,980 --> 00:02:29,320
You don't know that.

28
00:02:29,370 --> 00:02:30,540
I'm sure of it.

29
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:32,140
Okay.

30
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:36,320
If you accept the task,
she'll ask you for a written proposal.

31
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:37,710
A proposal?

32
00:02:38,030 --> 00:02:42,020
Outlining the venue, the program as well as
details from concierge to cloak service.

33
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:44,470
"I get so confused if it's not all written down."

34
00:02:44,470 --> 00:02:46,200
She'd say in that sweet voice of hers.

35
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:48,800
And after you've written it
all out like she said...

36
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:50,240
You've actually done this for her?

37
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:54,220
She would pick your work to pieces,
pointing out typo and grammar errors.

38
00:02:54,230 --> 00:02:57,640
After you finally fixed all these errors,
she starts vetoing the contents.

39
00:02:58,170 --> 00:03:00,590
I have a full-time job.

40
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:02,960
Why should I take so much crap
from her helping her out?

41
00:03:06,010 --> 00:03:11,370
So Aiko's dad runs a very established restaurant frequented by politicians.

42
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:15,800
Since she moves in more rarefied circles than us commoners...

43
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,470
her go-between were always hugely popular.

44
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:23,380
Kayoko would suck up to her
in hopes of getting invited to one.

45
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:26,750
Then Aiko became a cabin attendant
and stopped answering Kayoko's calls.

46
00:03:26,760 --> 00:03:29,340
So Kayoko started badmouthing her.

47
00:03:29,340 --> 00:03:32,620
Nevertheless, when Aiko suddenly asked her
to help with her post-reception party...

48
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:35,500
Kayoko was like "Anything for you."

49
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:37,370
Hilarious, isn't it?

50
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:42,280
Kayoko is a woman who spends
her downtime in beer bars.

51
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:46,430
How would she possibly know
anything about entertaining in Hawaii?

52
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:47,390
I guess so.

53
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:50,890
Although Aiko has her flaws,
she doesn't mean to be a pain in the neck.

54
00:03:50,890 --> 00:03:54,640
She just can't help saying
"Maybe there's a better place."

55
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:55,610
She's a terror to work for.

56
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,070
Sure sounds that way.

57
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:59,400
Congratulations, Tajima!

58
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:00,700
For me? Thanks!

59
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:02,730
– Tajima, congratulations!

60
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:07,920
Congratulations...

61
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:09,430
Way to go, Tajima.

62
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:11,330
Congratulations...

63
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:11,850
Thank you.

64
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:13,160
Is it a boy or a girl?

65
00:04:13,180 --> 00:04:14,460
– It's a boy.
– It's a boy!

66
00:04:14,860 --> 00:04:17,130
– Congratulations.
– You are too kind.

67
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,560
Congratulations!

68
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:28,400
The manuscripts are ready.

69
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:31,900
"Work Your Brain and Raise Your Pay."

70
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,850
"Walking Tour of 300 Famous Eateries."

71
00:04:34,090 --> 00:04:37,080
And "Live Longer by Laughing." 
Please go through them.

72
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:39,370
Efficient as ever.

73
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,680
Shall we do something on astrology next?

74
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:42,940
No.

75
00:04:46,670 --> 00:04:48,280
Let's create a guide book to Hawaii.

76
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:50,760
We've already done a bunch of those.

77
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,160
I know.

78
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:03,400
"Hawaii Now!"

79
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,830
"My Personal Hawaii."

80
00:05:05,390 --> 00:05:06,830
"Shopping in Hawaii."

81
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:08,200
"Hooray Hawaii."

82
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,210
"Feeling Hawaii."

83
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:10,250
"Hawaiian Ocean."

84
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,850
Enough. You're giving me a headache.

85
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:14,960
We published all these books
without making any trip to Hawaii.

86
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,750
Surprising, but clearly possible.

87
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,250
Hawaii is a hugely popular
travel destination now.

88
00:05:19,250 --> 00:05:23,450
If we were to compile a guide to
the places only locals go...

89
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,800
it will definitely be a hit.

90
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:30,740
And to be safe, we can throw in
a guide for Hawaiian weddings.

91
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,630
Weddings and local hangouts are totally 
unrelated. Rethink your strategy.

92
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:38,890
We can even include a top ten ranking
of Spam Musubi at the back.

93
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,670
I'm not convinced.

94
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,380
Boss.

95
00:05:51,180 --> 00:05:52,460
I saw something the other day.

96
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:58,170
That's a pretty nice car you bought.

97
00:06:00,890 --> 00:06:02,320
It's secondhand.

98
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:07,500
Every one else here
is struggling to pay their rent.

99
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:12,480
Owning a Porsche has always been my dream.

100
00:06:14,090 --> 00:06:15,720
If word gets out...

101
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:20,520
everyone might start
clamoring for a pay rise.

102
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:30,240
– Aiko? I'll plan your party for you.
– Really?

103
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:31,760
I'd like to go there right away.

104
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,700
Can you get me a ticket?

105
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:35,000
– Right away.
– Thanks. That'd be great.

106
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,560
– Bye.
– Bye.

107
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,760
I'm terribly sorry.

108
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:50,670
That's...

109
00:08:00,010 --> 00:08:02,780
Aloha. Welcome to the Moana Surfrider.

110
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:04,880
Thank you.

111
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,070
I'd like another.

112
00:09:07,470 --> 00:09:09,900
It goes down so easily, it's like juice.

113
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:10,680
{\pos(192,282)}Sure thing, ma'am.

114
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,720
You sure can drink.

115
00:09:22,410 --> 00:09:23,360
Are you alone, miss?

116
00:09:27,370 --> 00:09:28,480
She ignored me!

117
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:33,630
This is so typical of lonely women.

118
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:34,960
Thank you.

119
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:39,450
Imagine coming all this way
just to snub people.

120
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:44,390
It's always the lonely ones, I tell you.
It's written all over their faces.

121
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,150
Hey, waiter. A crazy guy just came in.

122
00:09:53,170 --> 00:09:54,740
Hey...!

123
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:57,110
You...

124
00:09:57,660 --> 00:09:58,620
You there!

125
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,980
You're not a guest here, are you?

126
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:06,480
You look like a bum.
What are you doing here?

127
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:07,280
Hey!

128
00:10:07,990 --> 00:10:08,830
What are you doing here?

129
00:10:08,830 --> 00:10:13,500
Are you collecting bottles for money?
 I happen to have some money with me.

130
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,720
I'll buy some bottles from you.
How much are you charging?

131
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:18,780
Hey, mister. He's a friend of mine.

132
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:25,220
Is that right?

133
00:10:41,290 --> 00:10:43,630
Are you hoping I'd be grateful or something?

134
00:10:44,610 --> 00:10:45,540
Excuse me?

135
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:48,760
You wanted to feel good
helping a poor guy out?

136
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,360
What do you mean?

137
00:10:52,060 --> 00:10:54,270
Well. I don't appreciate the gesture.

138
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:59,180
Even if you don't, there's no need to
highlight that fact, is there?

139
00:10:59,770 --> 00:11:03,450
I just wanted to shut that annoying
old man up, that's all.

140
00:11:03,610 --> 00:11:07,680
It worked, I feel better now.
We're not friend, you're free to go.

141
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:12,940
But if you plan to hang around,
stop flinging accusations...

142
00:11:13,390 --> 00:11:15,870
and join me for a drink, 
so we can talk trash about him.

143
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:24,520
You're pretty all right, I guess.

144
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:28,350
I get that all the time.

145
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:35,540
Listen...

146
00:11:37,020 --> 00:11:41,320
there's a full-moon party tonight
at Haleiwa Beach. Come if you'd like.

147
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:47,150
Sorry. Looks like
I've been invited to another party.

148
00:11:47,210 --> 00:11:49,850
You can come anytime.
The party will last all night.

149
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:58,280
The chairman will be attending the party,
so dress appropriately, okay?

150
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,110
Okay.

151
00:11:59,830 --> 00:12:01,200
Now, face each other.

152
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:05,390
Very nice. Stand a little closer.

153
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,240
Excuse me.

154
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,190
Let's try that again. Sorry.

155
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,160
Minori.

156
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:11,360
What's with the outfit?
You're really overdressed.

157
00:14:11,390 --> 00:14:13,610
You told me to dress appropriately.

158
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:16,010
Allow me to introduce.

159
00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:20,480
Akane...!

160
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:22,120
Go that way!

161
00:14:31,530 --> 00:14:33,070
Get off the horse.

162
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,110
{\pos(192,283)}Meet up again.

163
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,800
I guess as much. Thanks.

164
00:14:41,870 --> 00:14:43,130
You're welcome.

165
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:49,770
That's the Hawaii Polo Club chairman.
He said he'd teach me how to ride.

166
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:53,230
This is my friend. Yoshimura Akane.
She lives here.

167
00:14:53,790 --> 00:14:56,510
She'll help you plan the post-reception party.

168
00:14:59,950 --> 00:15:02,560
So you're the party planner.

169
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:07,530
The desire to serve others reflects 
mankind's most noble sentiment.

170
00:15:10,990 --> 00:15:15,000
I'm not in the habit of 
saying "Thanks" to dripping sarcasm.

171
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:20,670
Great. You'll get along just fine.

172
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,710
I'll leave the rest to you.

173
00:15:24,410 --> 00:15:26,440
No... wait.

174
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:40,920
Shall we ditch the party?
It's the same old crowd.

175
00:15:41,740 --> 00:15:43,580
You looked like you were 
having a ball though.

176
00:15:43,710 --> 00:15:47,260
No, I was just making it fun for them.

177
00:15:48,830 --> 00:15:51,290
But I haven't even met the groom yet.

178
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:54,760
Oh, he's hard at work
selling condominiums over there.

179
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,890
Better not bother him.

180
00:16:05,610 --> 00:16:07,230
Are you new to this kind of parties?

181
00:16:08,330 --> 00:16:09,000
Yes.

182
00:16:09,580 --> 00:16:10,990
Friends of Alan?

183
00:16:10,990 --> 00:16:12,300
Amazing guy.

184
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:15,180
His products are sold in all big countries.

185
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:15,850
Alan?

186
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:17,480
The "horse."

187
00:16:19,610 --> 00:16:21,390
He's the host.

188
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,970
This is his product.

189
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:25,850
Moisturizer that you wouldn't believe 
you can find them in the toilet.

190
00:16:26,910 --> 00:16:29,210
But you're here to have fun, so bottoms up.

191
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,040
What is this?

192
00:16:31,450 --> 00:16:32,780
Pineapple wine.

193
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,400
I'll pass.

194
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:42,040
Well...

195
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:47,530
before you speak, the president of
the winery is right over there.

196
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:58,080
– It's delicious!
– Thanks.

197
00:16:58,980 --> 00:16:59,510
Hi.

198
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:02,100
{\pos(192,283)}I think the flavor satisfies Japanese taste.

199
00:17:02,110 --> 00:17:03,690
{\pos(192,283)}Actually, she loves it.

200
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,300
{\pos(192,282)}Thank you very much.

201
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:13,050
That guy just used me to
talk to that president, didn't he?

202
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,160
He wore a suit to the party in Hawaii.

203
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:19,470
His kinds are like anteaters,
scavenging for money.

204
00:17:19,930 --> 00:17:20,900
Don't you mean hyenas?

205
00:17:21,010 --> 00:17:22,880
Let's hit a real party.

206
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,240
Is drink driving legal here?

207
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,560
I haven't had a drop.

208
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,280
So you aren't really drunk then?

209
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:43,420
You've got slam it shut really hard.

210
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:50,510
We'll drink at my place.

211
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:02,960
Stealing food from a party
is pretty cheap, don't you think?

212
00:18:04,010 --> 00:18:05,900
Well, you took the champagne, didn't you?

213
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:10,560
Yes, but I wouldn't bring along
a Tupperware to such a function.

214
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,640
– Don't you find it embarrassing?
– Speak for yourself...

215
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:15,310
– Akane!
– I'll never bring a Tupperware.

216
00:18:15,310 --> 00:18:17,720
Harassing the rich again?

217
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:20,160
Hey, Emi. Heading to work?

218
00:18:20,300 --> 00:18:23,100
Yeah, but do you mind if I have some?

219
00:18:23,370 --> 00:18:24,540
Sure.

220
00:18:24,810 --> 00:18:27,040
This is Aiko's friend.

221
00:18:27,050 --> 00:18:27,950
I'm Minori.

222
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:30,860
– I'm Emiko.
– And I'm Akane. Cheers.

223
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:32,670
Cheers!

224
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:34,650
Wearing Emi's clothes again?

225
00:18:34,730 --> 00:18:37,740
– Hey Mako.
– She's a painter.

226
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:40,080
No sugar daddies today?

227
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:42,570
I knew everyone there.

228
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,280
Is there anyone you don't know?

229
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:48,670
Sorry to drag you from that party.

230
00:18:49,210 --> 00:18:51,510
We'll go somewhere better.

231
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,900
There's a place called Loa Ridge.
That's where the rich men gather.

232
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:58,330
Just for the record,
I didn't come here to find a rich man.

233
00:18:58,540 --> 00:19:02,010
So are you saying you'd rather
scrape by than be rich.

234
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:06,850
I'm saying I'm not looking
for a man in the first place.

235
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:11,710
You prefer women?
How do I say "Lesbian" in Japanese?

236
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:13,280
You're already speaking in Japanese.

237
00:19:13,310 --> 00:19:15,420
We won't discriminate. It's fine.

238
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:19,930
Again for the record,
I am only attracted to men.

239
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:22,620
So Minori, what type of guys do you go for.

240
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:28,270
Well, let's see...

241
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,430
someone who'd tell me
when I've had enough to drink.

242
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:38,430
Of course, I wouldn't listen
and continue to drink.

243
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:44,240
He'll say, "Enough!" and take away my glass.

244
00:19:44,810 --> 00:19:48,410
But I'll probably hide
some whiskey under my bed.

245
00:19:51,550 --> 00:19:53,870
So you aspire to be an alcoholic?

246
00:19:54,620 --> 00:19:57,800
Get serious if you want your life to work out.

247
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:58,990
Who asked you?

248
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,990
A Japanese guy won't cut it for me.

249
00:20:01,180 --> 00:20:04,060
I want to stay here, so I need a green card.

250
00:20:04,060 --> 00:20:05,700
When's your visa expiring, Akane?

251
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:06,790
In three months.

252
00:20:06,990 --> 00:20:09,140
You've got to try harder
and hit the party more.

253
00:20:10,430 --> 00:20:12,830
So you'll settle for any American?

254
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:16,450
No way. If I have to settle for
some low-income housing over here...

255
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:18,960
I'd rather go back to my hometown
in Akita and grow rice.

256
00:20:18,970 --> 00:20:20,270
