but we also made place mats.

395
00:33:08,190 --> 00:33:09,090
Okay.

396
00:33:10,540 --> 00:33:12,370
{\pos(192,284)}After trying to make several designs,

397
00:33:12,450 --> 00:33:15,410
{\pos(192,234)}our company was sold
to a larger kitchenware company.

398
00:33:15,660 --> 00:33:18,850
{\pos(192,252)}So now, I'm just investing the money
we made from there.

399
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:24,950
{\pos(192,283)}You're living on dividends.

400
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:30,710
{\pos(192,235)}I'd very much like to hear any good
financial advice you might have for me.

401
00:33:33,180 --> 00:33:35,770
{\pos(192,283)}How about investment trust?

402
00:33:37,860 --> 00:33:39,880
{\pos(192,283)}How about talking at my place?

403
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:43,670
{\pos(192,282)}Or exchange-traded funds?

404
00:33:49,820 --> 00:33:50,840
Come on,

405
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:52,200
{\pos(192,283)}let's go.

406
00:33:56,810 --> 00:34:00,710
{\pos(192,236)}Listen, I'm living with a couple of girls
that I'm dating right now, but...

407
00:34:01,120 --> 00:34:02,950
{\pos(192,283)}I don't think you'd mind, do you?

408
00:34:03,860 --> 00:34:04,840
"Dating"?

409
00:34:05,550 --> 00:34:07,330
To put it simply, it's a trial period.

410
00:34:07,830 --> 00:34:11,670
He has several girls from among which
he'll choose on to be his girlfriend.

411
00:34:12,020 --> 00:34:14,950
So he can officially sleep
with several girls at the sane time.

412
00:34:15,130 --> 00:34:19,140
But I've never heard of anyone
living with all his dates.

413
00:34:19,410 --> 00:34:21,010
Sound efficient.

414
00:34:22,120 --> 00:34:23,460
It's a joke.

415
00:34:23,720 --> 00:34:25,930
So what happened?

416
00:34:27,090 --> 00:34:29,730
I'm not living in a harem.

417
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:33,400
I see.

418
00:34:34,340 --> 00:34:37,930
What about you, Minori?
You left with a Japanese businessman.

419
00:34:39,260 --> 00:34:40,210
Nothing happened.

420
00:34:41,620 --> 00:34:44,300
We had Ochazuke and Japanese wine.

421
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:45,500
You're in Hawaii, you know.

422
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:47,600
Then I went over to his place...

423
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:48,740
You went to his place?

424
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:52,970
Well...

425
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:57,040
sort of.

426
00:35:00,940 --> 00:35:02,920
Is this a warehouse?

427
00:35:03,610 --> 00:35:07,050
Yes, I rented it as a warehouse,
but it doubles as my house now.

428
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:08,800
Disappointed?

429
00:35:09,370 --> 00:35:10,820
Not really.

430
00:35:11,700 --> 00:35:14,720
I wear an expensive suit just to
look presentable for business dealings.

431
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:17,000
But actually, I'm struggling financially.

432
00:35:17,580 --> 00:35:19,640
I've had my share of setbacks.

433
00:35:22,770 --> 00:35:26,820
When I first took the plunge into
business, I sold toe socks.

434
00:35:27,010 --> 00:35:30,500
They rakes in enough profits
to fund my next venture.

435
00:35:31,190 --> 00:35:33,440
That's dry cleaning service.

436
00:35:34,410 --> 00:35:37,810
But that was a disaster.

437
00:35:38,490 --> 00:35:40,680
So next, I tried selling Konjac diet foods.

438
00:35:41,370 --> 00:35:43,000
That did all right.

439
00:35:43,670 --> 00:35:47,430
After that, it was charcoal-infused shampoo.

440
00:35:47,810 --> 00:35:50,890
I guess the advertising didn't work.

441
00:35:51,330 --> 00:35:52,950
It was a major flop.

442
00:35:53,270 --> 00:35:55,040
I made a comeback
with those green tea cookies.

443
00:35:55,470 --> 00:35:59,270
That did pretty well until sales flattened out.

444
00:35:59,380 --> 00:36:02,640
I used the profit to start 
my current restaurant.

445
00:36:05,520 --> 00:36:07,050
Don't you think you're being
way too adventurous?

446
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:11,120
That's what I need. I don't want
to lose the entrepreneurial spirit.

447
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:13,430
Perhaps you should take
into consideration local tastes.

448
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:16,220
No, that won't work.
The cookie business taught me a lesson.

449
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:20,230
To be well received in the States,
you need a unique Japanese touch.

450
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:26,480
For example, the Japanese dedication
to meticulous service.

451
00:36:26,690 --> 00:36:28,530
Or an "oriental" vibe.

452
00:36:28,770 --> 00:36:33,220
All these may seem normal to us,
but they really make an impact overseas.

453
00:36:33,730 --> 00:36:36,480
It's hard to see that in Japan.

454
00:36:38,990 --> 00:36:40,140
Want a drink?

455
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:48,530
And you left?

456
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,200
That guy did not impress me.

457
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:54,730
What's wrong with that?

458
00:36:55,580 --> 00:37:01,270
Back in Japan, my boss kept telling me
to publish anything that would sell.

459
00:37:01,650 --> 00:37:04,410
Travel guides, diet cookbooks,
pelvis correction exercise manuals...

460
00:37:05,110 --> 00:37:09,750
B-list restaurant guides,
shocking apocalyptic prophecies...

461
00:37:09,840 --> 00:37:13,030
lymphatic massage for a slimmer face 
and guides to the best spas in town.

462
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:14,240
That is...

463
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:17,730
I saw myself in him. It irked me.

464
00:37:19,830 --> 00:37:21,670
Do you understand what I'm saying?

465
00:37:25,180 --> 00:37:27,040
So you prefer a man who doesn’t work?

466
00:37:27,220 --> 00:37:30,730
No, a man should at least work
to support his loved ones.

467
00:37:31,980 --> 00:37:33,380
I see. So love begets money?

468
00:37:33,380 --> 00:37:39,280
Even if he's rich, he still needs to work
to maintain his fortune, right?

469
00:37:39,300 --> 00:37:41,850
That's not true.
It's not about how hard you work.

470
00:37:41,850 --> 00:37:46,160
The reality is that the rich get richer
and the poor remain poor, Minori.

471
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:49,970
That's warped logic.
There's more to life than that.

472
00:37:49,990 --> 00:37:52,350
Emi got married in a hurry
to secure a green card...

473
