in Hawaii. Fieldwork is progressing well."

511
00:39:52,930 --> 00:39:55,030
"But please send me more money...

512
00:39:55,030 --> 00:39:57,130
"as I'm running low on funds
Regards Minori."

513
00:40:07,650 --> 00:40:11,650
"Minori, I hope you're enjoying
your trip in Hawaii."

514
00:40:11,650 --> 00:40:15,450
"We need to talk after you get back.
Regards, Tajima."

515
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:42,180
Hello?

516
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:44,560
How's everything? Found a good spot
for the post-reception party?

517
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:49,290
That's...

518
00:40:49,690 --> 00:40:51,290
I'm spoilt for choice.

519
00:40:53,730 --> 00:40:55,260
I'm thinking out on the sea...

520
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:56,980
or maybe on a rooftop.

521
00:40:58,130 --> 00:41:01,190
Or how about a garden party?
Like in Kailua.

522
00:41:01,190 --> 00:41:04,440
That's a great idea.
I'm sure Satoshi will love it.

523
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:07,130
Let's get together to discuss it.

524
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:25,690
Welcome.

525
00:41:27,380 --> 00:41:28,450
This way, please.

526
00:41:41,020 --> 00:41:42,090
Are you alone today?

527
00:41:49,010 --> 00:41:54,610
I've been thinking about
what your friend said the other day.

528
00:41:57,890 --> 00:41:59,700
If I really care about you...

529
00:42:01,230 --> 00:42:03,640
I should find someone suitable for you.

530
00:42:04,490 --> 00:42:05,710
That's what true love is about.

531
00:42:08,060 --> 00:42:09,500
Have you been drinking?

532
00:42:10,590 --> 00:42:11,290
I'm not drunk.

533
00:42:17,370 --> 00:42:22,470
I've chosen a few clients of mine
who might be suitable for you.

534
00:42:27,060 --> 00:42:28,750
Please don't show this to anyone.

535
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:31,860
I'll be fired if I get found out.

536
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:36,720
You didn't have to do this.

537
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:42,420
If things don't go well with
any of these men...

538
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:46,760
I hope you'll choose me.

539
00:42:55,840 --> 00:43:00,300
There's going to be an Epicurean Club party
tomorrow afternoon at Loa Ridge.

540
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:03,180
Let's go together.

541
00:43:17,780 --> 00:43:20,240
Regarding your garden party idea...

542
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:20,760
Yes.

543
00:43:21,060 --> 00:43:22,280
I think it's great.

544
00:43:22,280 --> 00:43:23,310
You do?

545
00:43:24,030 --> 00:43:27,270
But I'm concerned about bathroom
facilities for female guests.

546
00:43:27,660 --> 00:43:32,170
You see, my friends and clients
tend to attract women wherever they go.

547
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:37,080
Hey, Tsutomu.

548
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:41,170
I heard you're going to 
Loa Ridge today. May I tag along?

549
00:43:43,070 --> 00:43:44,000
I don't think so.

550
00:43:44,340 --> 00:43:47,110
The pineapple wine venture fell through.

551
00:43:47,410 --> 00:43:50,890
But a guy I met at Alan's party
showed interest in Japanese food.

552
00:43:50,890 --> 00:43:52,710
I would like to meet him again.
Please do me a favor.

553
00:43:56,160 --> 00:43:56,870
All right then.

554
00:43:59,350 --> 00:44:02,860
Why don't you join us, Minori?
It's a party at Loa Ridge.

555
00:44:05,290 --> 00:44:05,990
Sure.

556
00:44:08,460 --> 00:44:09,450
Shall we?

557
00:44:10,130 --> 00:44:10,830
Thank you.

558
00:44:23,980 --> 00:44:27,060
I see you prefer successful guys.

559
00:44:28,270 --> 00:44:28,970
What?

560
00:44:49,750 --> 00:44:52,170
– This house looks really nice.
– Wait...

561
00:44:54,860 --> 00:44:55,560
Come here...

562
00:44:59,130 --> 00:45:01,320
The event is still going on.

563
00:45:02,670 --> 00:45:04,620
Isn't that why we are here?

564
00:45:04,620 --> 00:45:08,030
No, we have to wait for it to end...

565
00:45:08,030 --> 00:45:10,630
before we join the cocktail party.

566
00:45:14,470 --> 00:45:16,660
So we're commoners after all.

567
00:45:17,930 --> 00:45:19,840
Being here is a big deal in itself.

568
00:45:21,660 --> 00:45:23,410
Here, as in hanging around the periphery?

569
00:45:24,760 --> 00:45:26,160
Go home if you hate it so much.

570
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:38,150
Why are you dressed like that?

571
00:45:39,070 --> 00:45:40,900
This is my strategy.

572
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:42,410
She works for me.

573
00:45:44,340 --> 00:45:45,280
What's going on?

574
00:45:45,700 --> 00:45:48,530
So, Minori.
Finally interested in the rich?

575
00:45:48,990 --> 00:45:51,090
I'm just here for the drinks.

576
00:45:54,790 --> 00:45:56,040
I'll see how it's going inside.

577
00:46:28,420 --> 00:46:31,420
I wonder when they will
start throwing us table scraps?

578
00:46:32,970 --> 00:46:35,120
This is serious. Shut up.

579
00:46:37,370 --> 00:46:38,500
Get off your high horse.

580
00:46:39,290 --> 00:46:42,880
You're just waiting to pounce on change
that falls from their pockets.

581
00:46:45,540 --> 00:46:48,350
You don't understand because you've never
put your best foot forward, Minori.

582
00:46:49,530 --> 00:46:51,740
I'm sorry, but what are you trying to say?

583
00:46:52,510 --> 00:46:57,700
You've never taken anything seriously
enough to understand our feelings.

584
00:46:58,200 --> 00:47:00,290
Are you talking about yourself?

585
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:04,730
A person looking to marry rich
for a good life shouldn't talk.

586
00:47:04,730 --> 00:47:07,890
If you want money, why don't you
just get a job? Seriously.

587
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:11,080
Okay. I think we're good.

588
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:19,220
Let's go.

589
00:47:21,810 --> 00:47:24,000
It's better to look plain than tacky.

590
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:28,320
If you can't marry a rich man,
you can always be his mistress.

591
00:47:28,880 --> 00:47:30,070
Is that a joke?

592
00:47:54,620 --> 00:47:59,990
{\pos(192,235)}I think your son will be so thrilled to have 
a yacht for his junior high school graduation.

593
00:48:00,010 --> 00:48:01,830
{\pos(192,283)}Oh, that is fantastic.

594
00:48:07,450 --> 00:48:10,650
{\pos(192,236)}You know now the Japanese food
is widely accepted in the States?

595
00:48:10,670 --> 00:48:13,630
{\pos(192,236)}And my restaurant
is specialized in tea rice.

596
00:48:15,860 --> 00:48:16,660
Thank you.

597
00:48:21,830 --> 00:48:22,400
Hi.

598
00:48:22,570 --> 00:48:25,060
{\pos(192,285)}We met at Alan’s party the other day.

599
00:48:25,620 --> 00:48:27,820
{\pos(192,284)}I’m running a Japanese restaurant.

600
00:48:27,830 --> 00:48:30,860
{\pos(192,236)}You know now the Japanese food
is widely accepted in the States?

601
00:48:31,210 --> 00:48:34,050
{\pos(192,283)}And my restaurant is specialized in tea...

602
00:48:36,490 --> 00:48:37,260
Thank you.

603
00:48:45,820 --> 00:48:47,550
Do I act like a professional?

604
00:48:48,600 --> 00:48:52,280
No, be the flustered rookie.
Maybe you'll win their sympathy.

605
00:48:52,790 --> 00:48:54,440
In that case, shall I rip my sleeve as well?

606
00:48:54,740 --> 00:48:56,520
Those people love doing charity work.

607
00:48:57,140 --> 00:48:57,960
{\pos(192,283)}Hon!

608
00:49:01,180 --> 00:49:03,590
Listen, don't forget to take my advice.

609
00:49:05,030 --> 00:49:05,730
Hey!

610
00:49:06,100 --> 00:49:06,890
{\pos(192,283)}Hey, Hon.

611
00:49:07,700 --> 00:49:09,120
{\pos(192,283)}How's the night fishing the last time?

612
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:10,280
{\pos(192,283)}No good.

613
00:49:10,330 --> 00:49:12,330
{\pos(192,236)}You're still the record holder.

614
00:49:12,850 --> 00:49:13,560
Of course.

615
00:49:13,710 --> 00:49:16,300
{\pos(192,236)}Hon and I train hard against 
each other in trawling.

616
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:18,190
{\pos(192,283)}He's really good at it.

617
00:49:25,140 --> 00:49:28,520
{\pos(192,282)}May I introduce my new assistant, Akane?

618
00:49:36,310 --> 00:49:37,580
I feel so c-c-c-cold.

619
00:49:37,600 --> 00:49:39,350
{\pos(192,283)}You need something to put on?

620
00:49:39,380 --> 00:49:40,080
Yes.

621
00:49:57,000 --> 00:49:58,470
Don't you have a bigger glass?

622
00:50:33,250 --> 00:50:34,720
Hi, nice to meet you.

623
00:50:35,930 --> 00:50:38,210
{\pos(192,236)}Can I show you my business?

624
00:50:39,930 --> 00:50:40,630
Thank you.

625
00:50:54,680 --> 00:50:55,580
Finding this funny?

626
00:50:56,570 --> 00:50:59,560
No, it's boring actually.

627
00:50:59,930 --> 00:51:02,470
The world sure is run in a tedious way.

628
00:51:04,550 --> 00:51:06,490
Go ahead and sneer.

629
00:51:18,520 --> 00:51:21,440
That boring shop of yours
is never going to make it big.

630
00:51:21,440 --> 00:51:22,810
No, I'm sure it will be a hit.

631
00:51:23,330 --> 00:51:25,880
Japanese food is all the rage on the mainland.

632
00:51:27,750 --> 00:51:30,220
And yet you branded
your product as "tea rice"?

633
00:51:30,790 --> 00:51:35,350
If you're promoting Japanese cuisine,
you should call it "Ochazuke."

634
00:51:36,310 --> 00:51:39,360
That would be setting the bar too high.

635
00:51:42,470 --> 00:51:44,870
What a lame excuse.

636
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:48,360
Everyone calls "Sushi" by its name today.

637
00:51:48,930 --> 00:51:52,730
You're never going to strike big
with and attitude like that.

638
00:51:56,020 --> 00:51:59,780
Are you content to play second fiddle
or trendsetter all the time...

639
00:52:00,800 --> 00:52:04,010
and earning enough just to survive.

640
00:52:06,460 --> 00:52:07,590
What are you talking about?

641
00:52:11,190 --> 00:52:12,090
What I mean is...

642
00:52:14,260 --> 00:52:17,780
you should follow your heart.

643
00:52:18,250 --> 00:52:23,100
People can tell when you're half-hearted
about your own business. You fool!

644
00:52:26,370 --> 00:52:27,780
Go home.

645
00:52:27,980 --> 00:52:30,730
– Don't tell me what to do.
– Come on.

646
00:52:30,730 --> 00:52:32,430
– Let's go.
– Let's go of me!

647
00:52:34,940 --> 00:52:35,700
Ouch, that hurts.

648
00:52:42,800 --> 00:52:45,090
If you really believe in what you're doing...

649
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:50,470
you'll continue selling your product,
even if it's from the side of a truck.

650
00:52:52,380 --> 00:52:53,360
Listen.

651
00:52:55,360 --> 00:52:57,100
Instead of poking your nose into my business...

652
00:52:57,880 --> 00:52:59,790
you should worry about yourself.

653
00:53:22,970 --> 00:53:24,020
{\pos(192,283)}Ladies and gentlemen.

654
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:37,710
{\pos(192,283)}Let me introduce our new friend.

655
00:53:47,440 --> 00:53:48,680
{\pos(192,283)}Hello.

656
00:53:48,690 --> 00:53:50,510
{\pos(192,283)}My name is Tomoya Abe.

657
00:53:51,320 --> 00:53:52,860
{\pos(192,236)}Nice to see all of you.

658
00:53:54,790 --> 00:53:57,290
{\pos(192,283)}I'm the grandson of Kiotaka Abe.

659
00:54:00,590 --> 00:54:04,390
{\pos(192,236)}I grew up in Japan,
but when I was very young...

660
00:54:04,970 --> 00:54:08,310
{\pos(192,236)}I spent long vacations
here in my grandfather's house.

661
00:54:11,330 --> 00:54:14,540
{\pos(192,235)}My grandfather has already passed away...

662
00:54:15,090 --> 00:54:18,890
{\pos(192,235)}but those moments are
very precious memories to me.

663
00:54:26,270 --> 00:54:30,650
{\pos(192,236)}I'm sure that all of you have
unforgettable memories as well.

664
00:54:31,370 --> 00:54:33,180
{\pos(192,284)}So I'm not disappoint you.

665
00:54:33,190 --> 00:54:36,470
{\pos(192,284)}And, will honor your traditions...

666
00:54:36,960 --> 00:54:39,420
{\pos(192,236)}and I will rise to your expectations...

667
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:42,040
{\pos(192,236)}now that I'm accepted
as one of your members.

668
00:54:45,110 --> 00:54:46,640
I know you!

669
00:55:16,180 --> 00:55:18,450
Oyamada, where's your draft?

670
00:55:19,090 --> 00:55:20,670
Sorry, It's almost done.

671
00:55:23,150 --> 00:55:25,650
We'll publish a book on pelvis correction exercise.

672
00:55:26,360 --> 00:55:27,060
Yes, Boss.

673
00:55:32,110 --> 00:55:33,400
What should we do about the binding?

674
00:55:34,090 --> 00:55:35,730
I'm so sorry, Miss Oyamada.

675
00:55:36,360 --> 00:55:37,890
Could you do these too?

676
00:55:40,020 --> 00:55:41,800
Is the book on Jumbo Meals done?

677
00:55:41,800 --> 00:55:42,870
What about the facial slimming?

678
00:55:42,870 --> 00:55:45,670
The World's Ending in 2012 in a hurry!

679
00:55:47,530 --> 00:55:48,230
Yes.

680
00:55:49,040 --> 00:55:51,380
I know. I'm so sorry.

681
00:55:53,210 --> 00:55:55,030
I'll contact them immediately. I'm so sorry.

682
00:56:09,050 --> 00:56:09,650
Well...

683
00:56:10,480 --> 00:56:12,360
let's call it a night.

684
00:56:12,360 --> 00:56:14,160
No way!

685
00:56:15,390 --> 00:56:20,160
You think by getting drunk,
we can just forget everything by tomorrow?

686
00:56:20,160 --> 00:56:23,250
No, I don't. 
But we're going in circles.

687
00:56:23,980 --> 00:56:29,370
– Why doesn't anybody understand?
– I understand. I really do.

688
00:56:29,370 --> 00:56:33,200
I work the hardest in the company.

689
00:56:33,200 --> 00:56:34,810
Yes, you do.

690
00:56:35,160 --> 00:56:36,810
Don't you think it's ridiculous
that I don't get a pay rise?

691
00:56:36,810 --> 00:56:37,480
It's ridiculous.

692
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:39,360
I can't believe it.

693
00:56:40,460 --> 00:56:41,700
I'll resign tomorrow.

694
00:56:41,700 --> 00:56:44,540
Now, hold on a second.

695
00:56:44,540 --> 00:56:46,470
I'll do something about the money.

696
00:56:46,470 --> 00:56:48,550
I'll talk to accounting
or just claim more expenses.

697
00:56:49,990 --> 00:56:51,660
It's not about nickels and dimes.

698
00:56:51,660 --> 00:56:53,330
Yes...

699
00:56:53,330 --> 00:56:56,510
I'm asking, is this all I'm worth to them?

700
00:56:58,020 --> 00:56:59,250
But you know, Minori...

701
00:56:59,800 --> 00:57:02,850
without you, the company would fall apart.

702
00:57:03,480 --> 00:57:05,430
The company would go bust immediately.

703
00:57:06,250 --> 00:57:07,450
I mean it.

704
00:57:13,820 --> 00:57:14,860
Do you really think so?

705
00:57:15,890 --> 00:57:18,540
Of course! That's obvious.

706
00:57:19,110 --> 00:57:24,210
That's... those ungrateful brats...

707
00:57:27,870 --> 00:57:29,360
– Well said, Tajima.
– No...

708
00:57:29,660 --> 00:57:32,720
Please give me a break.
I can't drink anymore.

709
00:57:32,740 --> 00:57:35,920
Wait... wait a minute.

710
00:57:36,320 --> 00:57:40,640
Stop drinking. 
That's enough for this night.

711
00:57:40,640 --> 00:57:42,760
Oh, man.

712
00:57:43,950 --> 00:57:45,200
That sucks.

713
00:57:45,200 --> 00:57:47,520
It sure does for me.

714
00:57:47,720 --> 00:57:49,390
Hold on... that hurts.

715
00:57:49,910 --> 00:57:50,510
What do you want?

716
00:57:50,510 --> 00:57:52,110
– I don't know.
– Why...

717
00:57:52,110 --> 00:57:55,370
No... stop. That's enough.

718
00:57:57,510 --> 00:57:58,510
I'll take that.

719
00:58:04,130 --> 00:58:05,750
Are we done here?

720
00:58:50,600 --> 00:58:51,970
You were pretty smashed.

721
00:58:54,030 --> 00:58:55,420
Who are you?

722
00:58:56,460 --> 00:59:00,920
To put it simply, my family owns
a bunch of natural gas plants...

723
00:59:02,010 --> 00:59:04,000
as well as chemical and oil companies.

724
00:59:05,980 --> 00:59:08,190
In other words, you're very rich.

725
00:59:10,050 --> 00:59:11,900
Akane would be delighted.

726
00:59:13,290 --> 00:59:16,410
The gold diggers are always after me.

727
00:59:17,880 --> 00:59:21,130
Is that why you collect bottles
and make palm syrup.

728
00:59:22,190 --> 00:59:24,290
What a luxury that is.

729
00:59:24,970 --> 00:59:26,180
Are you a modern-day Robin Hood?

730
00:59:29,710 --> 00:59:34,400
I should be thinking about the business,
but I lack my father's talent.

731
00:59:35,850 --> 00:59:36,830
Is that so?

732
00:59:38,010 --> 00:59:39,250
What do I know?

733
00:59:40,330 --> 00:59:43,650
And, why do you drink so much?

734
00:59:45,260 --> 00:59:47,000
Well... it's my hobby.

735
00:59:49,290 --> 00:59:50,980
Like you collecting bottles.

736
00:59:54,360 --> 00:59:55,310
You don't want to talk about it?

737
01:00:00,100 --> 01:00:01,310
Is it a guy?

738
01:00:05,260 --> 01:00:05,890
Correct?

739
01:00:10,280 --> 01:00:14,170
I think it's a boy.

740
01:00:16,300 --> 01:00:18,340
Or was it a girl already?

741
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:36,930
Hell. I'll just tell you.

742
01:00:42,960 --> 01:00:45,770
A lot of stuff happened at work,
and I was really down.

743
01:00:45,770 --> 01:00:47,180
So I slept with a junior co-worker.

744
01:00:48,530 --> 01:00:50,410
But he's married.

745
01:00:52,180 --> 01:00:55,280
Since we're colleagues,

746
01:00:55,280 --> 01:00:56,960
I still have to see him everyday.

747
01:00:58,520 --> 01:00:59,350
And...

748
01:01:01,920 --> 01:01:05,380
I started bringing him home
with me after drinks.

749
01:01:07,690 --> 01:01:10,000
This went on for about four months.

750
01:01:14,820 --> 01:01:16,000
And then...

751
01:01:20,240 --> 01:01:22,810
I found out his wife was pregnant.

752
01:01:30,990 --> 01:01:32,270
It's really messed up.

753
01:01:38,060 --> 01:01:39,570
That's why you came to Hawaii?

754
01:01:57,550 --> 01:01:59,220
I don't know what I'm doing.

755
01:02:07,090 --> 01:02:08,980
I really ought to think it through.

756
01:02:10,000 --> 01:02:10,580
What is it?

757
01:02:14,700 --> 01:02:15,590
Nothing.

758
01:02:26,090 --> 01:02:27,050
When I first met you...

759
01:02:28,370 --> 01:02:29,650
at the hotel the other day,

760
01:02:31,600 --> 01:02:33,250
you tried to help me, didn't  you?

761
01:02:38,460 --> 01:02:40,140
Not that you needed any help.

762
01:02:40,970 --> 01:02:41,700
Still...

763
01:02:43,640 --> 01:02:47,760
I think that you helped me a lot 
even when you're already feeling down.

764
01:02:51,600 --> 01:02:52,550
Oh, stop.

765
01:03:20,680 --> 01:03:22,120
Is it really okay for me to join you?

766
01:03:22,510 --> 01:03:24,820
Yeah. It's like a celebration.

767
01:03:45,060 --> 01:03:48,790
(Hawaiian language)

768
01:03:55,680 --> 01:03:58,040
{\pos(192,284)}Auntie, I'd like to introduce Minori.

769
01:03:58,740 --> 01:04:00,050
Nice to meet you.

770
01:04:04,030 --> 01:04:07,330
(Hawaiian language)

771
01:04:07,910 --> 01:04:09,370
She says you're as pretty as a flower.

772
01:04:10,880 --> 01:04:11,840
Thank you.

773
01:04:13,140 --> 01:04:16,240
(Hawaiian language)

774
01:04:25,170 --> 01:04:27,130
It's her husband who passed away.

775
01:04:29,550 --> 01:04:32,070
I just saw him surfing the other day.

776
01:04:48,100 --> 01:04:53,800
(Hawaiian language)

777
01:04:59,720 --> 01:05:00,420
Let's go.

778
01:07:30,280 --> 01:07:33,300
Loa Ridge was a disaster,
but today will be different.

779
01:07:34,550 --> 01:07:35,790
Our target today is...

780
01:07:35,790 --> 01:07:37,800
to jog along this course.

781
01:07:38,420 --> 01:07:40,490
When he comes, run alongside him.

782
01:07:41,140 --> 01:07:42,490
Make conversation so that
he'll remember you...

783
01:07:42,490 --> 01:07:44,290
then we see him again
at the party this weekend.

784
01:07:44,750 --> 01:07:45,370
What do you think?

785
01:07:46,160 --> 01:07:47,320
That's a good plan...

786
01:07:47,960 --> 01:07:48,790
right?

787
01:07:52,650 --> 01:07:54,330
It's okay, Honma.

788
01:07:54,330 --> 01:07:55,050
No.

789
01:07:55,730 --> 01:07:59,260
We only have three 
potential candidates left.

790
01:07:59,260 --> 01:08:00,420
It's enough.

791
01:08:00,420 --> 01:08:01,260
No.

792
01:08:01,260 --> 01:08:02,310
I got it.

793
01:08:02,310 --> 01:08:03,230
No, you don't.

794
01:08:03,730 --> 01:08:06,470
You still don't get how I care for you.

795
01:08:06,470 --> 01:08:07,550
Yes, I do.

796
01:08:07,550 --> 01:08:08,850
No, you don't.

797
01:08:08,850 --> 01:08:11,120
Do you have any idea
how valuable this information is?

798
01:08:11,120 --> 01:08:12,890
I said, that's enough!

799
01:08:15,360 --> 01:08:18,910
I've made up my mind
the moment you showed me this.

800
01:08:18,910 --> 01:08:19,810
You've made up your mind?

801
01:08:27,230 --> 01:08:29,120
I've made up my mind to marry you.

802
01:08:35,780 --> 01:08:38,290
Akane... no!

803
01:08:38,290 --> 01:08:40,720
You don't have to shout.
I can hear you fine.

804
01:08:40,720 --> 01:08:43,050
You should find a man
who will give you happiness!

805
01:08:43,050 --> 01:08:44,820
That's why I've chosen you!

806
01:08:48,980 --> 01:08:54,190
I only played along since 
you went to the trouble to do this.

807
01:08:54,540 --> 01:08:55,610
So it's enough.

808
01:08:58,580 --> 01:08:59,500
A-A-Akane!

809
01:08:59,500 --> 01:09:02,410
That's why I don't need this anymore.

810
01:09:02,510 --> 01:09:03,780
My papers!

811
01:09:07,280 --> 01:09:08,200
Oh well.

812
01:09:15,920 --> 01:09:16,700
Akane.

813
01:09:55,640 --> 01:09:59,390
You're dating that rich guy from
Loa Ridge? Are you crazy?

814
01:09:59,390 --> 01:10:01,460
Who are you calling crazy?

815
01:10:01,460 --> 01:10:03,250
I can just hear Emi now.

816
01:10:03,250 --> 01:10:07,680
"Minori's boyfriend is a Loa Ridge guy
while you've settled for Honma."

817
01:10:07,680 --> 01:10:09,580
– You're dating Honma?
– Never mind that.

818
01:10:09,580 --> 01:10:10,700
Why...?

819
01:10:10,700 --> 01:10:12,330
Forget about Honma.

820
01:10:12,330 --> 01:10:16,200
Are you going to be living at Loa Ridge?

821
01:10:16,200 --> 01:10:17,120
Akane!

822
01:10:17,900 --> 01:10:18,880
Our table's over here.

823
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:20,560
Yes, I can see that.

824
01:10:21,160 --> 01:10:23,340
You know what? Honma's kind of cute.

825
01:10:23,340 --> 01:10:25,020
Don't make fun of my boyfriend.

826
01:10:25,020 --> 01:10:26,520
Can you not be paranoid?

827
01:10:26,520 --> 01:10:27,440
Akane!

828
01:10:28,490 --> 01:10:29,880
Shall I place the order for you?

829
01:10:29,880 --> 01:10:31,680
Yeah, by all means.

830
01:10:31,680 --> 01:10:33,130
So come on, tell me.

831
01:10:33,130 --> 01:10:34,140
Akane...!

832
01:10:34,140 --> 01:10:35,340
What is it now?

833
01:10:35,340 --> 01:10:38,100
– There's no Caesar salad.
– Any salad will do.

834
01:10:39,280 --> 01:10:41,060
Hey, they've got mushroom salad.

835
01:10:41,060 --> 01:10:42,760
That's great. Get that.

836
01:10:43,300 --> 01:10:44,920
– So...
– What?

837
01:10:44,920 --> 01:10:47,730
you agree a rich guy is still the best?

838
01:10:47,730 --> 01:10:50,260
Akane, you think all rich people
are jerks, don't you?

839
01:10:50,400 --> 01:10:51,570
That's discrimination.

840
01:10:55,350 --> 01:10:57,680
You've finally awoken to love.

841
01:10:58,240 --> 01:11:00,200
Will love really beget money?

842
01:11:00,200 --> 01:11:01,550
That was what you said.

843
01:11:01,550 --> 01:11:02,770
Forget what I said.

844
01:11:02,770 --> 01:11:06,190
How did you hook up with him?
Can you tell me?

845
01:11:06,770 --> 01:11:08,300
It's nothing worth mentioning.

846
01:11:08,890 --> 01:11:10,490
Don't be coy.

847
01:11:10,490 --> 01:11:13,780
You told him your sob story about dating
a married man and he consoled you?

848
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:16,930
Well...

849
01:11:17,570 --> 01:11:19,460
That's pretty close to the mark.

850
01:11:19,460 --> 01:11:22,800
That goes against what you told Honma.
Remember what you said?

851
01:11:22,800 --> 01:11:24,820
Guy who take advantage of women
when they are down are the worst.

852
01:11:24,820 --> 01:11:26,590
Jerks who resort to 
such manipulative tricks...

853
01:11:26,590 --> 01:11:27,940
are either the sort who borrow small change
without intending to pay it back...

854
01:11:27,940 --> 01:11:29,770
or the sort who makes things difficult for
the staff at convenience stores.

855
01:11:29,770 --> 01:11:31,570
Which type are you? 
Or are you both?

856
01:11:31,950 --> 01:11:33,530
Wow, you've got a good memory.

857
01:11:33,530 --> 01:11:35,480
That's because I intend to marry him.

858
01:11:35,480 --> 01:11:37,200
Really? Congratulations!

859
01:11:37,200 --> 01:11:38,700
Like I said, this is not about me.

860
01:11:38,700 --> 01:11:39,560
Everything all right?

861
01:11:40,260 --> 01:11:42,230
They are getting married!

862
01:11:42,350 --> 01:11:42,850
What?

863
01:11:48,890 --> 01:11:50,110
Congratulations.

864
01:11:52,560 --> 01:11:53,570
That's wonderful.

865
01:11:54,270 --> 01:11:55,990
Now comes the hard part.

866
01:11:55,990 --> 01:11:58,310
Forget about Honma.

867
01:12:02,370 --> 01:12:03,040
What is it?

868
01:12:07,520 --> 01:12:08,650
Akane...

869
01:12:10,080 --> 01:12:12,190
You've got something 
precious going on there.

870
01:12:13,120 --> 01:12:16,690
So stop talking about me already!

871
01:12:16,690 --> 01:12:20,490
You're so annoying!

872
01:12:40,330 --> 01:12:43,430
{\pos(192,236)}Hey, whatever happened
to the pipeline in Azerbaijan?

873
01:12:43,600 --> 01:12:46,780
{\pos(192,283)}Since that conflict in Georgia,

874
01:12:46,960 --> 01:12:49,510
{\pos(192,252)}we had to abandon the project
right, Tomoya?

875
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:50,600
Yeah.

876
01:12:50,960 --> 01:12:52,160
{\pos(192,283)}It seems.

877
01:12:52,850 --> 01:12:54,270
{\pos(192,283)}It seems?

878
01:12:54,970 --> 01:12:56,980
{\pos(192,283)}Why aren't you more cooperative?

879
01:13:03,310 --> 01:13:04,810
He wants me to be more serious.

880
01:13:06,220 --> 01:13:07,090
{\pos(192,283)}Tomoya.

881
01:13:10,560 --> 01:13:12,320
{\pos(192,283)}Do whatever you like.

882
01:14:10,780 --> 01:14:12,970
How is it going with the guide book?

883
01:14:14,380 --> 01:14:14,830
Hey.

884
01:14:15,100 --> 01:14:16,190
– Tajima.
– Yes.

885
01:14:16,190 --> 01:14:17,660
Has she called you?

886
01:14:18,250 --> 01:14:18,760
No.

887
01:14:20,500 --> 01:14:22,690
She contacted you though.

888
01:14:22,690 --> 01:14:25,410
She checked out of her hotel
and I can't reach her on her phone.

889
01:14:26,290 --> 01:14:28,250
She should be there for two weeks,
but it's been twenty days.

890
01:14:29,090 --> 01:14:31,870
You don't suppose
she will stay for good, do you?

891
01:14:32,440 --> 01:14:35,320
She's on a tourist visa, though.

892
01:14:35,320 --> 01:14:36,950
How long is her visa valid for?

893
01:14:38,340 --> 01:14:40,000
I believe it's three months.

894
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:41,620
We can't wait that long.

895
01:14:42,710 --> 01:14:43,860
– Tajima.
– Yes.

896
01:14:44,890 --> 01:14:46,250
Go to Hawaii and find her.

897
01:14:48,470 --> 01:14:48,970
Eh?

898
01:15:01,920 --> 01:15:03,860
Saki...?

899
01:15:04,890 --> 01:15:06,130
Look. According to this,

900
01:15:06,130 --> 01:15:08,720
they will let you fly a Cessna.

901
01:15:08,720 --> 01:15:10,510
A Cessna?  Really?

902
01:15:10,510 --> 01:15:12,760
Is that awesome or what?

903
01:15:14,290 --> 01:15:17,490
– That rocks...! 
– A Cessna, no less!

904
01:15:17,490 --> 01:15:19,300
– Awesome!

905
01:15:19,300 --> 01:15:20,520
Yes..!

906
01:15:20,520 --> 01:15:22,820
– I know! We'll be pilots.
– Awesome!

907
01:15:22,820 --> 01:15:23,300
Wait.

908
01:15:23,300 --> 01:15:23,860
Excuse me.

909
01:15:23,860 --> 01:15:27,170
– Look at this.
– What? We can play with dolphins.

910
01:15:27,170 --> 01:15:29,440
Really? Dolphins are so cute!

911
01:15:29,440 --> 01:15:31,260
Pardon me. Excuse me.

912
01:15:31,260 --> 01:15:33,680
– Dolphins are the cutest!
– This is so exciting!

913
01:15:34,200 --> 01:15:36,100
Really want to go to Hawaii!

914
01:15:36,100 --> 01:15:39,330
You've got to take the night cruise.
That's where I met my ex.

915
01:15:39,330 --> 01:15:41,060
– Really?
– Sure.

916
01:15:41,520 --> 01:15:43,620
– You want to meet guys, don't you?
– Excuse me.

917
01:15:43,620 --> 01:15:44,510
Yes, I do.

918
01:15:46,140 --> 01:15:49,260
I swear to God this will change your life.

919
01:15:49,260 --> 01:15:51,690
All right! This is so exciting!

920
01:15:51,690 --> 01:15:53,360
So exciting!

921
01:15:53,360 --> 01:15:56,090
Excuse me. Please excuse me.

922
01:15:56,910 --> 01:15:58,570
It's going to be great.

923
01:15:59,110 --> 01:16:00,330
There's an amazing place...

924
01:16:00,390 --> 01:16:03,410
just beyond the next mountain.

925
01:16:05,070 --> 01:16:06,620
I found it with Ryan.

926
01:16:07,770 --> 01:16:10,720
There's a hidden river deep in the jungle.

927
01:16:11,770 --> 01:16:13,840
You'll be amazed when you see it.

928
01:16:17,060 --> 01:16:18,000
It will blow you away.

929
01:16:30,530 --> 01:16:31,690
What are you doing?

930
01:16:32,360 --> 01:16:33,670
See for yourself.

931
01:16:37,900 --> 01:16:39,690
I'll be parking the truck ahead.
Come and have some.

932
01:16:56,380 --> 01:16:57,110
Your friend?

933
01:16:58,300 --> 01:16:58,700
What?

934
01:16:59,610 --> 01:17:01,110
Oh... yes.

935
01:17:12,950 --> 01:17:13,550
All right.

936
01:17:14,010 --> 01:17:16,490
{\pos(192,252)}I take one large
Lomi Lomi Chazuke...

937
01:17:16,490 --> 01:17:16,990
Lomi Lomi. Okay

938
01:17:17,260 --> 01:17:19,540
{\pos(192,283)}and one large Salmon Chazuke.

939
01:17:19,850 --> 01:17:23,180
{\pos(192,283)}I have a medium Poke Dashi Chazuke...

940
01:17:23,180 --> 01:17:25,710
{\pos(192,283)}and one medium Ume Chazuke.

941
01:17:26,110 --> 01:17:27,070
{\pos(192,283)}Just a moment, please.

942
01:17:27,070 --> 01:17:28,630
What's up, Tomoya?
How are you doing?

943
01:17:29,700 --> 01:17:30,460
{\pos(192,283)}Here you are.

944
01:17:30,500 --> 01:17:31,590
– Thanks.
– Thank you.

945
01:17:34,000 --> 01:17:35,090
Pick anything you like.

946
01:17:56,670 --> 01:17:58,840
{\pos(192,284)}Thank you. Please come again.

947
01:17:58,860 --> 01:17:59,360
Thanks.

948
01:18:08,400 --> 01:18:09,130
What do you think?

949
01:18:09,690 --> 01:18:11,840
It's delicious!

950
01:18:11,840 --> 01:18:13,750
It goes great with Hawaiian food.

951
01:18:16,610 --> 01:18:20,300
I infused Japanese flavors
into local cuisine.

952
01:18:20,950 --> 01:18:23,980
This way, the locals can get
a taste of Japanese food...

953
01:18:24,380 --> 01:18:27,780
and the Japanese can also 
draw closer to Hawaiians.

954
01:18:28,090 --> 01:18:28,730
It feels like...

955
01:18:29,440 --> 01:18:31,440
I'm erasing borders.

956
01:18:33,310 --> 01:18:34,850
It sounds interesting.

957
01:18:40,590 --> 01:18:42,300
Do you always set up shop here?

958
01:18:42,300 --> 01:18:43,160
No.

959
01:18:43,160 --> 01:18:48,020
I go downtown in the mornings,
and come here in the evenings.

960
01:18:48,360 --> 01:18:52,280
At night, I target the tourists
in Waikiki after they hit the pubs.

961
01:18:54,940 --> 01:18:56,620
Sounds busy.

962
01:19:00,290 --> 01:19:04,760
Well, you told me to sell my products from 
a truck if my store didn't work out.

963
01:19:18,230 --> 01:19:20,450
Are you going out with him?

964
01:19:24,320 --> 01:19:25,650
Yeah... you can say that.

965
01:19:28,710 --> 01:19:30,930
He's from a rich family, right?

966
01:19:32,530 --> 01:19:33,310
Apparently.

967
01:19:44,440 --> 01:19:45,240
Good for you.

968
01:19:53,450 --> 01:19:54,640
{\pos(192,282)}Excuse me!

969
01:19:56,330 --> 01:19:58,040
A commoner's got to work.

970
01:19:58,970 --> 01:20:01,680
I'm better off working anyway.
It's a lot of fun.

971
01:20:04,540 --> 01:20:05,780
Did it sound like sour grapes?

972
01:20:06,720 --> 01:20:08,450
No, I know what you mean.

973
01:20:09,990 --> 01:20:11,260
I'm a commoner too.

974
01:20:14,940 --> 01:20:16,930
{\pos(192,283)}Give me one large Poke Chazuke.

975
01:20:16,940 --> 01:20:18,820
{\pos(192,283)}Hi! I come over.

976
01:20:19,580 --> 01:20:20,500
See you then.

977
01:21:13,260 --> 01:21:14,250
Are you off to work?

978
01:21:16,540 --> 01:21:18,590
I have to get approval for merger plans.

979
01:21:19,950 --> 01:21:22,170
I don't know much about
the workings of the company...

980
01:21:22,170 --> 01:21:23,600
but I'm a board member after all.

981
01:21:27,920 --> 01:21:29,290
Aren't you a hard worker then.

982
01:21:31,840 --> 01:21:33,710
All I do is nod.

983
01:21:47,400 --> 01:21:48,860
Where shall we meet for dinner?

984
01:21:49,620 --> 01:21:54,130
Sorry, I promised to meet Aiko tonight.
I'll call you when I'm done.

985
01:22:14,840 --> 01:22:16,300
– Sorry.
– Thank you.

986
01:22:17,320 --> 01:22:18,030
Excuse me,

987
01:22:18,040 --> 01:22:20,360
{\pos(192,283)}have you seen this lady?

988
01:22:20,360 --> 01:22:20,900
No.

989
01:22:23,710 --> 01:22:24,390
Excuse me,

990
01:22:24,720 --> 01:22:26,590
{\pos(192,283)}have you seen this lady?

991
01:22:28,040 --> 01:22:29,300
No...?

992
01:24:25,200 --> 01:24:27,180
Are you close to Mr. Abe's son?

993
01:24:29,140 --> 01:24:31,160
Yes... just recently.

994
01:24:32,540 --> 01:24:33,850
I guess word travels.

995
01:24:34,910 --> 01:24:38,370
The four of us should 
get together sometime.

996
01:24:38,570 --> 01:24:39,950
Good idea!

997
01:24:41,180 --> 01:24:44,570
My friend's having a gallery opening.
Do come with him.

998
01:24:46,750 --> 01:24:49,950
Have you heard when the next
Epicurean Club party will be held?

999
01:24:50,950 --> 01:24:51,740
No, I haven't.

1000
01:24:55,160 --> 01:24:56,390
I need to use the washroom.

1001
01:25:04,890 --> 01:25:08,580
{\pos(192,236)}I set up a mobile Ochazuke 
food truck in the parking lots...

1002
01:25:08,590 --> 01:25:11,780
{\pos(192,285)}so that I can sell at different locations.

1003
01:25:12,310 --> 01:25:14,490
{\pos(192,283)}I like the mobility idea. That's smart.

1004
01:25:15,240 --> 01:25:20,780
{\pos(192,236)}I'm a little unsure about the menu,
mixing local dishes with Ochazuke.

1005
01:25:20,790 --> 01:25:22,190
{\pos(192,283)}Do you think that would work?

1006
01:25:22,230 --> 01:25:28,790
{\pos(192,236)}Well, I'm already selling Poke Chazuke
and Spam Chazuke.

1007
01:25:28,790 --> 01:25:30,420
{\pos(192,284)}They're quite popular.

1008
01:25:31,260 --> 01:25:32,680
{\pos(192,283)}I see. Okay.

1009
01:25:37,320 --> 01:25:38,730
{\pos(192,283)}Well...

1010
01:25:39,510 --> 01:25:42,290
{\pos(192,283)}aren't you Mr Abe's...?

1011
01:25:45,290 --> 01:25:49,030
{\pos(192,285)}I am like Ohana(family) to Mr Abe.

1012
01:25:56,300 --> 01:25:57,720
{\pos(192,284)}Mr Kamada?

1013
01:25:58,380 --> 01:26:02,480
{\pos(192,236)}Tomoya wants to order 
your Ochazuke takeout again.

1014
01:26:02,780 --> 01:26:05,460
{\pos(192,283)}So you're friends with Mr Abe as well?

1015
01:26:05,470 --> 01:26:07,310
{\pos(192,283)}Yes, of course!

1016
01:26:09,490 --> 01:26:12,940
{\pos(192,236)}Now, I see why you get
such awesome ideas.

1017
01:26:13,800 --> 01:26:14,240
Okay.

1018
01:26:14,700 --> 01:26:15,760
{\pos(192,283)}I'm interested.

1019
01:26:17,240 --> 01:26:18,500
{\pos(192,283)}See you.

1020
01:26:18,580 --> 01:26:19,620
{\pos(192,283)}It's nice to see you.

1021
01:26:20,980 --> 01:26:22,590
{\pos(192,283)}Can you show me some more of this?

1022
01:26:23,930 --> 01:26:25,150
{\pos(192,283)}Another one...

1023
01:26:25,170 --> 01:26:25,720
is...

1024
01:26:26,150 --> 01:26:27,300
{\pos(192,283)}Tonkatsu.

1025
01:26:29,070 --> 01:26:30,070
{\pos(192,283)}Loco Moco.

1026
01:26:30,150 --> 01:26:31,960
{\pos(192,283)}Loco Moco? I like Loco Moco.

1027
01:26:31,990 --> 01:26:33,540
{\pos(192,283)}Lau Lau Chazuke.

1028
01:26:33,560 --> 01:26:35,120
{\pos(192,283)}That's a good idea.

1029
01:26:39,730 --> 01:26:40,630
What can I do for you?

1030
01:26:43,970 --> 01:26:47,060
Well, Akane...

1031
01:26:47,060 --> 01:26:49,900
do you know that Ochazuke hawker?

1032
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:51,960
"Ochazuke hawker"?

1033
01:26:55,940 --> 01:27:01,040
He was at the Loa Ridge party
trying to find backers for his business.

1034
01:27:01,730 --> 01:27:03,230
Are you interested in that?

1035
01:27:03,230 --> 01:27:04,560
Of course not!

1036
01:27:08,530 --> 01:27:09,270
Anyway.

1037
01:27:10,420 --> 01:27:12,090
He doesn't need my money and...

1038
01:27:12,680 --> 01:27:16,030
he has no lack of interested investors.

1039
01:27:18,220 --> 01:27:20,180
What's the big deal about it anyway?

1040
01:27:24,390 --> 01:27:26,340
So you don't like Ochazuke that much.

1041
01:27:26,870 --> 01:27:28,500
– Thank you.
– Thank you.

1042
01:27:30,700 --> 01:27:33,340
Minori, will you be at your
boyfriend's place today as well?

1043
01:27:34,160 --> 01:27:36,400
Why don't you join us for drinks?

1044
01:27:38,440 --> 01:27:39,390
Minori!

1045
01:27:42,360 --> 01:27:43,690
Thanks for your help back there.

1046
01:27:43,690 --> 01:27:44,660
How did it go?

1047
01:27:45,200 --> 01:27:47,200
He's going to invest.

1048
01:27:47,200 --> 01:27:49,080
Really? That's wonderful.

1049
01:27:49,080 --> 01:27:51,040
It's all thanks to you, Minori.

1050
01:27:51,040 --> 01:27:52,990
This calls for a celebration, right?

1051
01:27:55,600 --> 01:27:57,520
– Did he agree to it all?
– I can't thank you enough.

1052
01:27:57,520 --> 01:27:59,050
Everything went so smoothly.

1053
01:27:59,050 --> 01:27:59,810
I see.

1054
01:28:01,250 --> 01:28:02,460
I'm so relieved.

1055
01:28:02,460 --> 01:28:03,420
What did he say?

1056
01:28:03,420 --> 01:28:05,290
He took the initiative to discuss details.

1057
01:28:05,290 --> 01:28:07,910
– I see. So he was into it?
– Totally.

1058
01:28:10,040 --> 01:28:11,780
Excuse me...

1059
01:28:12,430 --> 01:28:13,850
Have you seen this lady?

1060
01:28:15,360 --> 01:28:15,860
No?

1061
01:28:16,490 --> 01:28:18,000
We don't know her.

1062
01:28:18,000 --> 01:28:19,100
Sorry to bother you.

1063
01:28:19,100 --> 01:28:20,100
Thank you.

1064
01:28:23,920 --> 01:28:26,460
Where on earth are you, Minori?

1065
01:28:28,160 --> 01:28:28,960
Excuse me...

1066
01:28:30,300 --> 01:28:32,600
{\pos(192,283)}have you seen this lady?

1067
01:28:34,450 --> 01:28:36,150
{\pos(192,283)}No. Sorry.

1068
01:28:36,150 --> 01:28:38,130
{\pos(192,283)}Thank you.

1069
01:28:52,090 --> 01:28:52,890
I see.

1070
01:28:54,170 --> 01:28:56,490
So you'll be expanding to the mainland.

1071
01:28:58,350 --> 01:29:01,990
Up until now. I've been
so concerned with just staying afloat.

1072
01:29:02,670 --> 01:29:05,870
I had to come up with new ideas
if the previous one didn't work out.

1073
01:29:06,650 --> 01:29:11,910
There was constant pressure and,
I think I lost myself for a while.

1074
01:29:13,850 --> 01:29:15,010
I know what you mean.

1075
01:29:15,870 --> 01:29:16,470
Really?

1076
01:29:20,100 --> 01:29:23,100
I did a lot of thinking
after I closed down my restaurant.

1077
01:29:24,660 --> 01:29:27,200
I still remember the first time
I came to the States.

1078
01:29:29,010 --> 01:29:31,660
When my dad was posted to the States...

1079
01:29:32,340 --> 01:29:34,340
Mom and I visited him once.

1080
01:29:37,100 --> 01:29:39,050
At the Arizona countryside.

1081
01:29:40,350 --> 01:29:43,120
My father and I borrowed bicycles
and rode around in the neighborhood.

1082
01:29:44,260 --> 01:29:46,200
We had burgers at a diner.

1083
01:29:48,400 --> 01:29:51,580
That memory stuck in my mind.

1084
01:29:55,300 --> 01:29:57,390
Remember what you said to me?

1085
01:29:57,390 --> 01:29:59,670
You said I've got to know
what I want to do in life.

1086
01:30:09,510 --> 01:30:13,710
Can I get your advice again when I start
scouting for shops in the mainland?

1087
01:30:16,360 --> 01:30:17,500
Sure.

1088
01:30:18,130 --> 01:30:22,120
But wouldn't it be better if
you consult an expert instead?

1089
01:30:26,490 --> 01:30:30,970
I'd prefer someone who knows me
over an any business expert.

1090
01:30:44,360 --> 01:30:45,100
Sure.

1091
01:30:52,390 --> 01:30:55,900
They are probably just good friends.

1092
01:30:58,130 --> 01:31:00,510
I can tell from their eyes
there's something going on.

1093
01:31:02,540 --> 01:31:03,500
What are you going to do?

1094
01:31:04,900 --> 01:31:10,050
Crush that Ochazuke hawker
with your wealth and influence?

1095
01:31:14,580 --> 01:31:17,760
I thought I've found a woman
who can accept who I am.

1096
01:31:19,410 --> 01:31:21,900
Any girl would say "yes" to you.

1097
01:31:21,900 --> 01:31:24,330
But it's not for her!

1098
01:31:26,760 --> 01:31:28,040
You've lost me.

1099
01:31:30,690 --> 01:31:33,420
It doesn't matter to her who I am.

1100
01:31:36,050 --> 01:31:38,340
You mean she'll dump you
in spite of your social status.

1101
01:31:39,750 --> 01:31:42,560
What's so great about that Ochazuke guy?

1102
01:31:43,720 --> 01:31:46,360
You're upsetting yourself
by letting your imagination run wild.

1103
01:31:46,360 --> 01:31:47,260
So silly.

1104
01:31:47,990 --> 01:31:50,990
I thought I've found a woman
who can accept who I am.

1105
01:31:52,750 --> 01:31:54,830
We're just going in circles now.
May I go already?

1106
01:31:55,390 --> 01:31:56,700
Hold on...

1107
01:31:57,140 --> 01:32:00,210
– You're just repeating yourself.
– Just one more drink.

1108
01:32:00,210 --> 01:32:00,930
One more drink.

1109
01:32:00,940 --> 01:32:03,770
{\pos(192,252)}Check out this marlin!
I break the new record.

1110
01:32:05,830 --> 01:32:09,160
– Get your hands off. 
– Just one more drink...

1111
01:32:12,070 --> 01:32:13,460
Akane!

1112
01:32:15,890 --> 01:32:18,300
Are you still trying to 
land yourself a rich guy?

1113
01:32:18,960 --> 01:32:20,510
What's with you?

1114
01:32:20,510 --> 01:32:22,100
Answer me!

1115
01:32:22,100 --> 01:32:24,140
Of course not! Why would I?

1116
01:32:24,140 --> 01:32:25,550
Then what are you doing?

1117
01:32:25,550 --> 01:32:28,850
Honma, come and join us.

1118
01:32:29,710 --> 01:32:31,510
How dare you!

1119
01:32:31,980 --> 01:32:32,830
Honma.

1120
01:32:33,690 --> 01:32:35,260
Where did you get that huge tuna?

1121
01:32:35,590 --> 01:32:37,560
{\pos(192,283)}I made it. I did it!

1122
01:32:37,580 --> 01:32:39,320
Minori, can you believe this?

1123
01:32:40,910 --> 01:32:41,420
What's this?

1124
01:32:41,870 --> 01:32:44,560
Honma doesn't trust me!

1125
01:32:44,900 --> 01:32:46,370
That's totally understandable.

1126
01:32:46,680 --> 01:32:49,650
I won't marry someone who doesn't trust me!

1127
01:32:51,040 --> 01:32:51,870
Minori.

1128
01:32:52,940 --> 01:32:55,130
Do you really think he's good enough?

1129
01:32:59,000 --> 01:32:59,850
Me?

1130
01:32:59,850 --> 01:33:02,010
Minori, you should apologize him?

1131
01:33:02,010 --> 01:33:05,470
Yeah, you're going to regret it
if he dumps you.

1132
01:33:06,390 --> 01:33:09,310
{\pos(192,283)}Tomoya, this is my new record, bro!

1133
01:33:11,140 --> 01:33:11,740
{\pos(192,283)}My battle...

1134
01:33:11,750 --> 01:33:13,700
{\pos(192,283)}I hate trawling!

1135
01:33:13,710 --> 01:33:15,270
{\pos(192,283)}It's stupid!

1136
01:33:15,910 --> 01:33:17,630
{\pos(192,283)}Shut the f*ck up!

1137
01:33:17,900 --> 01:33:20,600
{\pos(192,285)}Tomoya, you never know the high of it.

1138
01:33:21,760 --> 01:33:24,360
Do you really think that Ochazuke
dude is good enough for you?

1139
01:33:25,090 --> 01:33:27,500
You're mistaken. We just ran into
each other at the restaurant.

1140
01:33:27,500 --> 01:33:29,570
He's better than someone collecting bottles.

1141
01:33:30,580 --> 01:33:33,000
Is that how you judge people?

1142
01:33:33,000 --> 01:33:34,700
Look who's talking!

1143
01:33:34,700 --> 01:33:37,800
I gave up a lot of opportunities
just to be with you, Honma!

1144
01:33:38,020 --> 01:33:38,780
I knew it!

1145
01:33:39,070 --> 01:33:40,660
So you do regret choosing me!

1146
01:33:40,660 --> 01:33:41,700
No, I don't!

1147
01:33:41,700 --> 01:33:44,180
You will definitely regret it.
You'd better kiss and make up.

1148
01:33:44,180 --> 01:33:47,600
What's wrong with me?

1149
01:33:47,920 --> 01:33:49,790
Seriously, who are you?

1150
01:33:49,790 --> 01:33:51,280
What do you want to be?

1151
01:33:53,770 --> 01:33:56,890
Minori, Mr Abe runs a major
international company...

1152
01:33:56,890 --> 01:33:57,960
You...!

1153
01:33:58,840 --> 01:34:02,160
will do anything to land a rich husband!

1154
01:34:02,160 --> 01:34:03,840
How dare you!

1155
01:34:04,710 --> 01:34:06,600
Yeah, I'll do anything!

1156
01:34:11,450 --> 01:34:14,700
Darn you!

1157
01:34:22,210 --> 01:34:23,500
Bring it on!

1158
01:34:25,340 --> 01:34:26,390
Come on!

1159
01:34:26,390 --> 01:34:27,550
We need to talk.

1160
01:34:28,820 --> 01:34:29,690
Mr Abe!

1161
01:34:30,550 --> 01:34:31,680
It's all a misunderstanding.

1162
01:34:31,680 --> 01:34:34,010
Minori only has eyes for you.

1163
01:34:34,430 --> 01:34:35,610
That's what I think.

1164
01:34:35,610 --> 01:34:37,500
Who is this guy?

1165
01:34:37,500 --> 01:34:38,620
Oh, pardon me.

1166
01:34:38,620 --> 01:34:43,690
I run a condominium
and yacht resale company.

1167
01:34:48,070 --> 01:34:50,690
– Here's my another name card.
– Get out of my way!

1168
01:34:53,910 --> 01:34:55,310
No... stop it!

1169
01:35:00,950 --> 01:35:02,450
We'll let them work it out.

1170
01:35:05,540 --> 01:35:06,600
Akane!

1171
01:35:07,600 --> 01:35:13,280
We're nothing but 
convenient tools to guys like him.

1172
01:35:13,280 --> 01:35:15,480
We're not human to them.

1173
01:35:16,060 --> 01:35:17,050
Don't you understand?

1174
01:35:17,580 --> 01:35:18,850
Just let go of him.

1175
01:35:30,040 --> 01:35:32,080
Wait...!

1176
01:35:35,070 --> 01:35:38,170
The problems lies with yourself!
Do something about it!

1177
01:35:42,310 --> 01:35:43,790
What did I do?

1178
01:35:45,410 --> 01:35:47,600
So you're nice to everyone?

1179
01:35:59,610 --> 01:36:01,390
For being so nice to me...

1180
01:36:02,560 --> 01:36:04,560
Thank you!

1181
01:36:05,830 --> 01:36:06,900
Are you okay?

1182
01:36:09,120 --> 01:36:09,920
Are you okay?

1183
01:36:11,100 --> 01:36:11,990
Calm down!

1184
01:36:14,380 --> 01:36:16,170
You'll kill him!

1185
01:36:16,910 --> 01:36:18,670
He's killing Honma!

1186
01:36:19,640 --> 01:36:21,300
Just calm down!

1187
01:36:40,030 --> 01:36:41,230
Well...

1188
01:36:42,600 --> 01:36:44,290
You all carry on then.

1189
01:36:48,320 --> 01:36:49,940
We shall make a move.

1190
01:36:58,400 --> 01:36:59,510
Goodbye.

1191
01:37:04,960 --> 01:37:06,260
I'm really sorry.

1192
01:37:07,390 --> 01:37:08,250
I'm okay now.

1193
01:37:08,650 --> 01:37:09,430
Really?

1194
01:37:21,570 --> 01:37:22,600
I'm so sorry.

1195
01:37:23,770 --> 01:37:25,260
I had a drop too much.

1196
01:37:26,590 --> 01:37:27,250
It's okay.

1197
01:37:32,990 --> 01:37:34,560
Is your business doing well?

1198
01:37:35,440 --> 01:37:36,060
Well...

1199
01:37:36,780 --> 01:37:38,600
I'm just starting out.

1200
01:37:39,700 --> 01:37:40,410
I see.

1201
01:37:52,440 --> 01:37:54,990
If you need any help,
you can come to me.

1202
01:37:56,140 --> 01:37:56,640
Thanks.

1203
01:38:04,800 --> 01:38:07,550
I'm sorry I went ballistic.

1204
01:38:10,090 --> 01:38:11,460
That's what keeps you...

1205
01:38:12,020 --> 01:38:14,200
from getting ahead.

1206
01:38:15,920 --> 01:38:16,710
I'm sorry.

1207
01:38:33,520 --> 01:38:35,450
So when's the weddings?

1208
01:38:35,850 --> 01:38:38,130
I don't know if I'll go through with it.

1209
01:38:40,080 --> 01:38:41,600
I mean the wedding ceremony.

1210
01:38:44,560 --> 01:38:45,400
Thank god.

1211
01:38:46,090 --> 01:38:47,900
You worry too much.

1212
01:39:24,320 --> 01:39:25,150
What is it?

1213
01:39:25,800 --> 01:39:26,610
Do you know him?

1214
01:39:30,870 --> 01:39:31,570
No.

1215
01:39:33,180 --> 01:39:34,060
Just a stranger.

1216
01:39:47,760 --> 01:39:49,010
Sorry about today.

1217
01:39:49,540 --> 01:39:50,130
No worries.

1218
01:39:52,690 --> 01:39:54,480
We'll celebrate another day.

1219
01:39:59,750 --> 01:40:00,380
But...

1220
01:40:01,720 --> 01:40:03,400
won't he get angry again?

1221
01:40:15,380 --> 01:40:18,400
I'll be busy planning my trip
to scout for shops anyway.

1222
01:40:24,250 --> 01:40:24,800
See you then.

1223
01:41:41,930 --> 01:41:42,610
I'm sorry.

1224
01:42:40,830 --> 01:42:41,600
What's wrong?

1225
01:42:58,730 --> 01:43:02,070
{\pos(192,236)}What happened to the 
natural gas plant in the Caspian sea?

1226
01:43:02,190 --> 01:43:04,530
{\pos(192,283)}Well, nothing much has happened.

1227
01:43:05,030 --> 01:43:07,840
{\pos(192,236)}Well, who is the principal company,
The UK again?

1228
01:43:07,960 --> 01:43:11,160
{\pos(192,236)}No way. 
Azerbaijan will have thirty percent...

1229
01:43:11,280 --> 01:43:13,330
{\pos(192,283)}the two Japanese will take ten percent...

1230
01:43:13,500 --> 01:43:15,460
{\pos(192,283)}and we have fifteen percent.

1231
01:43:15,660 --> 01:43:19,590
{\pos(192,236)}You'll still have to stick with the
Russian pipeline. We can't live without it.

1232
01:43:20,040 --> 01:43:24,210
{\pos(192,235)}I don't think Europe wants Russia
to have any control of the business anymore.

1233
01:43:24,590 --> 01:43:26,170
{\pos(192,284)}Absolutely true.

1234
01:43:26,470 --> 01:43:29,220
{\pos(192,252)}Even if you extend it to 
the black sea through Georgia...

1235
01:43:29,390 --> 01:43:31,470
{\pos(192,283)}There's a problem in South Ossetia.

1236
01:43:31,600 --> 01:43:33,810
{\pos(192,285)}You don't know when Russia will be involved.

1237
01:43:33,930 --> 01:43:36,440
{\pos(192,283)}Thus you cannot pass Armenia.

1238
01:43:37,270 --> 01:43:42,070
{\pos(192,236)}You lay it from Turkey to
the Adriatic Sea out to Italy.

1239
01:43:42,440 --> 01:43:45,510
{\pos(192,237)}What if we let that joint venture company
from Switzerland handle it?

1240
01:43:45,520 --> 01:43:48,410
{\pos(192,252)}I don't think even they
could remedy the situation.

1241
01:43:49,570 --> 01:43:51,070
{\pos(192,284)}It's a fool's errand.

1242
01:43:52,330 --> 01:43:55,620
{\pos(192,283)}Hey, you want to give it a try?

1243
01:43:56,830 --> 01:43:58,210
{\pos(192,283)}Sure.

1244
01:43:58,500 --> 01:43:59,880
{\pos(192,284)}I'll do it.

1245
01:44:02,420 --> 01:44:06,720
{\pos(192,236)}I'll be flying over there next month
and be in charge there.

1246
01:44:07,510 --> 01:44:10,800
{\pos(192,283)}I won't be back until I accomplish the project.

1247
01:44:15,430 --> 01:44:17,020
{\pos(192,283)}I see.

1248
01:44:21,710 --> 01:44:22,700
I give you credit.

1249
01:44:24,170 --> 01:44:25,500
– Thank you.
– That's impressive.

1250
01:45:29,310 --> 01:45:31,250
Aiko, Satoshi.

1251
01:45:31,650 --> 01:45:33,000
Congratulations!

1252
01:45:34,460 --> 01:45:37,570
I've been asked to make a speech.

1253
01:45:37,570 --> 01:45:39,440
My name is Endo Kayoko.

1254
01:45:46,460 --> 01:45:49,250
Because they're holding their wedding
here in Hawaii,

1255
01:45:49,620 --> 01:45:51,200
I did a little research.

1256
01:45:58,250 --> 01:46:01,490
Is she going to quote from a travel guide?

1257
01:46:01,490 --> 01:46:03,100
You've got to admire her style.

1258
01:46:05,850 --> 01:46:06,600
Let's see...

1259
01:46:07,700 --> 01:46:11,950
In Hawaii, people greet
each other with the word "Aloha."

1260
01:46:13,260 --> 01:46:14,300
This word...

1261
01:46:18,150 --> 01:46:19,600
"Aloha" means...

1262
01:46:20,750 --> 01:46:21,300
Love.

1263
01:46:22,490 --> 01:46:23,200
Pride.

1264
01:46:24,190 --> 01:46:24,930
Wisdom.

1265
01:46:25,770 --> 01:46:26,640
Welcome.

1266
01:46:27,120 --> 01:46:28,050
Trust.

1267
01:46:28,830 --> 01:46:29,800
Hello.

1268
01:46:30,100 --> 01:46:31,070
Goodbye.

1269
01:46:31,700 --> 01:46:32,600
Thank you...

1270
01:46:33,140 --> 01:46:34,520
and I love you.

1271
01:46:35,090 --> 01:46:37,290
It is a beautiful word...

1272
01:46:37,290 --> 01:46:39,460
with a wealth of meaning.

1273
01:46:40,670 --> 01:46:42,020
But when translated literally...

1274
01:46:43,890 --> 01:46:47,660
"Alo" from Aloha means "to share."

1275
01:46:49,000 --> 01:46:52,600
And "ha" from Aloha means "breathing"

1276
01:46:53,830 --> 01:46:56,400
Put together, it means "shared breathing."

1277
01:46:58,180 --> 01:47:01,350
In Japanese, we have a similar phrase...

1278
01:47:01,350 --> 01:47:03,230
that means a perfect match.

1279
01:47:05,000 --> 01:47:06,970
In a marriage...

1280
01:47:07,900 --> 01:47:10,920
it's not wealth or looks that matters,

1281
01:47:11,630 --> 01:47:16,240
but compatibility and finding whether
someone who is your perfect match.

1282
01:47:17,300 --> 01:47:18,660
It sure is.

1283
01:47:19,340 --> 01:47:21,000
It really is.

1284
01:47:25,000 --> 01:47:26,220
With that meaning in mind,

1285
01:47:26,900 --> 01:47:28,500
I think Aiko and Satoshi...

1286
01:47:29,080 --> 01:47:31,900
can be said to be
a perfect match made in heaven.

1287
01:47:34,850 --> 01:47:35,780
Aloha!

1288
01:47:58,120 --> 01:47:59,500
You're next, Akane.

1289
01:48:00,640 --> 01:48:02,950
We'll just be having a party at the shop.

1290
01:48:02,950 --> 01:48:04,300
– Really?
– Yes.

1291
01:48:10,720 --> 01:48:12,160
Will you stop that?

1292
01:48:12,160 --> 01:48:13,500
What's wrong?

1293
01:48:13,500 --> 01:48:15,470
I'm just getting my money's worth.

1294
01:48:20,000 --> 01:48:21,250
Have you found a job yet?

1295
01:48:24,230 --> 01:48:26,560
I'm thinking of becoming an editor
for a free town paper...

1296
01:48:26,850 --> 01:48:27,800
or a waitress.

1297
01:48:28,490 --> 01:48:29,620
The editor sounds good.

1298
01:48:31,370 --> 01:48:32,530
I don't know.

1299
01:48:33,070 --> 01:48:35,850
But what a shame...

1300
01:48:36,200 --> 01:48:39,600
you could have been living up at Loa Ridge.

1301
01:48:40,970 --> 01:48:42,270
That's true.

1302
01:49:28,250 --> 01:49:29,600
How was the States?

1303
01:49:29,910 --> 01:49:31,450
I forgot, this is the States too.

1304
01:49:31,780 --> 01:49:32,880
Are you waiting for someone?

1305
01:49:35,200 --> 01:49:36,280
I see.

1306
01:49:38,010 --> 01:49:39,100
Let me help you.

1307
01:49:39,200 --> 01:49:40,020
Thank you.

1308
01:49:46,500 --> 01:49:49,240
So where will you be setting up
your first shop on the mainland?

1309
01:49:50,180 --> 01:49:52,900
I think I'll start at Washington D.C..

1310
01:49:53,550 --> 01:49:54,550
Because it's the capital?

1311
01:49:56,220 --> 01:49:57,130
That's funny.

1312
01:49:57,130 --> 01:49:59,150
I visited Texas too. Great place.

1313
01:49:59,670 --> 01:50:00,600
As I expected...

1314
01:50:01,000 --> 01:50:03,200
a nation-wide chain store
should start from the capital.

1315
01:50:05,350 --> 01:50:06,500
Sounds exciting.

1316
01:50:09,710 --> 01:50:11,250
How was the wedding?

1317
01:50:11,830 --> 01:50:13,210
It was beautiful.

1318
01:50:14,100 --> 01:50:15,250
Were you envious?

1319
01:50:18,780 --> 01:50:20,210
I can imagine.

1320
01:50:28,450 --> 01:50:29,550
Is he well?

1321
01:50:32,290 --> 01:50:33,970
The successor to Abe corporation.

1322
01:50:37,990 --> 01:50:39,450
I haven't seen him in a while.

1323
01:50:41,010 --> 01:50:41,690
Really?

1324
01:50:42,180 --> 01:50:42,780
Why not?

1325
01:50:47,190 --> 01:50:49,180
Because I'm a commoner.

1326
01:51:00,870 --> 01:51:02,060
Actually, I...

1327
01:51:07,710 --> 01:51:08,900
I...

1328
01:51:20,350 --> 01:51:25,010
When do you suppose 
I'll be able to get married?

1329
01:51:31,300 --> 01:51:32,590
Soon, I suppose.

1330
01:51:36,370 --> 01:51:37,100
Really?

1331
01:51:37,520 --> 01:51:38,280
Yeah.

1332
01:51:38,780 --> 01:51:39,860
I'm sure of it.

1333
01:51:41,740 --> 01:51:42,800
You think so?

1334
01:51:43,220 --> 01:51:44,010
Yes.

1335
01:51:45,090 --> 01:51:45,970
Are you sure?

1336
01:51:45,970 --> 01:51:46,640
Yes.

1337
01:51:46,640 --> 01:51:47,470
Do you mean it?

1338
01:51:47,470 --> 01:51:48,190
Of course.

1339
01:51:51,080 --> 01:51:51,890
I guess...

1340
01:51:53,220 --> 01:51:54,470
I'll take your word for it.

1341
01:52:06,240 --> 01:52:07,600
Excuse me.

1342
01:52:08,750 --> 01:52:10,280
Here's the manuscript from Minori.

1343
01:52:10,280 --> 01:52:11,460
Is it done?

1344
01:52:12,510 --> 01:52:13,640
Here you go.

